distribution of the 1991-92 sample, the trend disappeared (prevalence 
1980-81:1.35%).
CONCLUSION: There was no increase in an individual's risk of diabetes. However 
the crude prevalence tended to increase because of the changing age structure of 
the population. On-going studies are needed to follow the prevalence of diabetes 
during the next decade.

