that of women in Norway and Sweden is partly a transitional phenomenon caused by 
excessive death rates for women born between the two World Wars. Data on smoking 
prevalence by birth cohort and age indicate that a high percentage of Danish 
women in these cohorts were smokers throughout their adult life.

